Condition: What is the effect on herring?

A: As we catch more small pelogics, there are less of them in the sea

Condition: What is the effect on winter flounder?

A: the winter flounder is a predator of the flatfish. Less flatfish, so more white flounder

Condition: What is the effect on yellowtail flounder?

A: Yellowtail flounder and flatfish dont compete in any way and neither is a predator of the other

Condition: What is the effect on skates?

A: Skates depend on elasmobranchs to eat. Less elasmobranchs means less skates

Condition: What is the effect on cod?

A: If there are less elasmobranchs, cod have less competition so their population increases

Condition: What is the effect on haddock?

A: Haddock may depend on elasmobranchs for some part of the food chain. Less elasmobranchs means slightly less haddock

Condition: What is the effect on windowpane?

A: Windowpanes may eat elasmobranchs. less elasmobranchs mean less windowpanes
